15/03/2005
PRISTINA, Kosovo, Serbia-Montenegro -- Kosovo President Ibrahim Rugova escaped injury when a bomb exploded near his car Tuesday (15 March) morning.
At least one vehicle in the president's convoy was damaged.
The blast broke windows;
flying glass reportedly injured one person.
Rugova was heading for a meeting with EU foreign policy chief Javier Solana at the time.
(AP, AFP, Reuters, BBC - 15/03/05)
